    "description": [
        {
            "text": "\"Permittivity\" is a physical quantity that describes how an electric field affects, and is affected by a dielectric medium, and is determined by the ability of a material to polarize in response to the field, and thereby reduce the total electric field inside the material.  Permittivity is often a scalar valued quantity, however in the general case it is tensor-valued.",
            "lang": "en"
        }
